+ Combine Tables\nwith Joins
++ Join Types
+++ INNER
++++_ Matching rows only
+++ LEFT
++++_ All left rows + NULLs for no match
+++ RIGHT
++++_ All right rows + NULLs for no match
+++ FULL
++++_ All rows from both tables
+++ SEMI
++++_ Left rows with matches (no right cols)
+++ ANTI
++++_ Left rows without matches
+++ CROSS
++++_ Cartesian product
++ SQL: JOIN ... ON / USING
-- PySpark: df.join()
---_ on= column or condition
---_ how= join type string
-- Column Name Conflicts
---_ Same name → pass as string
---_ Avoids duplicate columns
@endmindmap
